article.headline: Jacksonville St. 79, Tennessee Tech 74
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Ala. (AP) -- Jonathan Toles had 21 points to help lead Jacksonville State to a 79-74 win over Tennessee Tech Thursday night. The Gamecocks (2-12, 0-6 Ohio Valley Conference) led 42-37 going into the intermission and won by that same margin. Toles was one of five double figure scorers for the Gamecocks. Amadou Mbodji had 19 points and Nick Murphy added 15 more. Will Ginn and Erwin Staten chipped in with 11 points apiece. Anthony Fisher led the Golden Eagles (6-10, 3-3 OVC) with 16 points. Daniel Northern and Frank Davis had 14 points each, and Amadi McKenzie added 12 more. Northern also had 14 rebounds.
